The paper describes a practical method for developing custom software products, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The method involves using a store of libraries and tools independent from the OS, which could be considered a programming language (cs.PL) or distributed computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also discusses the benefits of repeatable deterministic builds, which could be relevant to the deep learning (cs.DL) or machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
